+
+### Review Findings
+
+- [x] [Review][Patch][Resolved Decision] **D1** — Ship the shared YAML loader project. Round 2 Resolved Decision `P-shared-1` was marked `[x]` but the shared library was not extracted; `Generation/Program.cs:1027-1063` and `ClientGenerationTests.cs:1798-1948` independently re-implement `LoadYaml`/`RequiredMapping`/`RequiredScalar`/`ReadStringSequence`/`TryReadRequestSchema`/parameter enumeration. Resolution: **add a shared project** (e.g., `src/Hexalith.Folders.Client/Generation/Hexalith.Folders.Client.Generation.Shared.csproj`) containing the YAML loader helpers and `OperationModel`/`ParameterModel` types, referenced by both `Generation` and `Hexalith.Folders.Client.Tests`. Eliminates drift between test parser and generator parser. Affects AC 11, AC 14.
+- [x] [Review][Patch][Resolved Decision] **D2** — Convert `ResolveField` inline switch to a `Dictionary<(string SchemaName, string Field), FieldModel>` registry. Round 2 Resolved Decision `P-registry-1` was marked `[x]` but Round 3 shipped an inline switch expression at `src/Hexalith.Folders.Client/Generation/Program.cs:674-688` instead of the agreed registry shape. Resolution: **convert to a `static readonly Dictionary<(string, string), FieldModel>` initialized at file scope, with per-entry `// hexalith.folders.v1.yaml:NNNN` comments naming the spine lines for each special-case field, and have `ResolveField` call `TryGetValue` first**. Affects AC 11, AC 15.
+- [x] [Review][Patch][Resolved Decision] **D3** — Accept workspace request parameter-order swap as canonical spine evolution and add detection surface. Workspace request signatures changed from `(folderId, taskId, workspaceId)` to `(folderId, workspaceId, taskId)` for `LockWorkspaceRequest`, `PrepareWorkspaceRequest`, `ReleaseWorkspaceLockRequest`; `BranchRefPolicyRequest` parameter changed from `providerBindingRef` to `folderId` (`src/Hexalith.Folders.Client/Generated/HexalithFoldersIdempotencyHelpers.g.cs:163-219, 186-201`). Same C# `string` types means positional callers silently mis-hash. Resolution (compatible with AC 9 — no release docs, no CLI/MCP work): **(a) add a documentation paragraph in `docs/contract/sdk-generation-and-idempotency-helpers.md` describing the rename and how to detect via `HelperSchemaVersion`, (b) emit `public const string HelperSchemaVersion = "20260516";` in the generated helpers file so downstream consumers can branch on it, (c) tighten the helper-presence reflection test in `ClientGenerationTests.cs` to assert parameter NAMES + ORDER match the spine-derived path-parameter list (merges with patch P14 below)**. Affects AC 4, AC 13.
+- [x] [Review][Patch] ProblemDetails / ProblemDetailsParseDiagnostic re-parse on every property access [`src/Hexalith.Folders.Client/Generated/HexalithFoldersIdempotencyHelpers.g.cs:101-118`] — both expression-bodied properties call `TryReadProblemDetails` per access, so 10 reads = 10 deserializations. Under retry loops this becomes a hot path. Inverted-looking branch in `TryGetProblemDetails` (`is null ? problem : null`) also obscures intent. Memoize the parse result in a thread-safe lazy backing field and split into one parse + two getter projections.
+- [x] [Review][Patch] `NormalizeGeneratedHelperHash` regex is fragile [`src/Hexalith.Folders.Client/Generated/HexalithFoldersIdempotencyHelpers.g.cs:88-89`, `src/Hexalith.Folders.Client/Generation/Program.cs:1145`] — character class `[0-9a-fA-F_]+` admits `_` which SHA-256 hex never contains; replacement string injects fixed 4-space indentation so any tab/2-space variant breaks `IsCurrent`; trailing comment or differing EOL after the semicolon evades the anchor. Tighten to `(?m)^(?<indent>\s*)public const string GeneratedHelpersSha256 = "[0-9a-fA-F]{64}";$` and emit `${indent}` in the replacement so indentation round-trips.
+- [x] [Review][Patch] `VerifyCurrentDetailed` swallows `FileNotFoundException` with only the exception type name [`src/Hexalith.Folders.Client/Generated/HexalithFoldersIdempotencyHelpers.g.cs:70-72`] — callers cannot tell *which* of the three input files is missing. Include the offending path (already known at the call site) and the exception message in the diagnostic.
+- [x] [Review][Patch] Magic cast `(FileMutationRequestFileOperationKind)2` for Remove [`src/Hexalith.Folders.Client/Generated/HexalithFoldersIdempotencyHelpers.g.cs:303`] — if NSwag changes enum ordering Remove silently maps to a different member. Replace with `Enum.Parse<FileMutationRequestFileOperationKind>("Remove")` at the call site, or have the generator emit a compile-time check that asserts the ordinal.
+- [x] [Review][Patch] DateTime vs DateTimeOffset canonicalization is asymmetric [`src/Hexalith.Folders.Client/Idempotency/HexalithIdempotencyHasher.cs:1283-1285, 1406-1414`] — `DateTime` throws on `Kind != Utc`; `DateTimeOffset` silently calls `ToUniversalTime()`. Two clients sending the same logical instant via `DateTimeOffset` get equal hashes, via `DateTime` get exceptions. Unify: either both throw on non-UTC, or both convert. Document the choice.
+- [x] [Review][Patch] Decimal `-0m` vs `0m` produce different hashes [`src/Hexalith.Folders.Client/Idempotency/HexalithIdempotencyHasher.cs:1416-1422`] — `decimal.GetBits(-0m)` sets the sign bit; `decimal.GetBits(0m)` does not. Normalize the sign bit when the integer magnitude is zero, or explicitly document the distinction with a fixture test.
+- [x] [Review][Patch] `GetEnumWireValue` mishandles `[Flags]` / composite enum values [`src/Hexalith.Folders.Client/Idempotency/HexalithIdempotencyHasher.cs:1335-1341`] — `SingleOrDefault` throws `InvalidOperationException` on `"A, B"` composite; dead `?.` null-conditional fallback because `member` was already thrown on. Detect `[Flags]` up front and reject; iterate `Type.GetFields()` for stable resolution.
+- [x] [Review][Patch] `ParseArguments` does not validate values aren't flag-shaped [`src/Hexalith.Folders.Client/Generation/Program.cs:1118-1137`] — a misordered `--repository-root --contract /path/x.yaml` invocation produces `{"--repository-root": "--contract"}`. Validate `!values[i+1].StartsWith("--", Ordinal)` and fail-closed with the offending position.
+- [x] [Review][Patch] `EnsureDeclaredOrder` error message omits offending fields [`src/Hexalith.Folders.Client/Generation/Program.cs:556-559`, `src/Hexalith.Folders.Client/Idempotency/HexalithIdempotencyHasher.cs:1375-1394`] — message says "must be in ordinal-ascending order" without naming which fields violated. Include the previous + current field name in the diagnostic.
+- [x] [Review][Patch] `EnsureParameter` accepts an unused `openApiName` parameter [`src/Hexalith.Folders.Client/Generation/Program.cs:697-707`] — discarded via `_ = openApiName;`. Either drop the parameter from the signature or actually use it to verify the spine-to-method name mapping.
+- [x] [Review][Patch] `HelperGenerationTargetRegeneratesWhenContractSpineChanges` leaks temp directories [`tests/Hexalith.Folders.Client.Tests/ClientGenerationTests.cs:1628-1650`] — creates `tempRoot` but never deletes (no try/finally). On Windows CI temp dirs accumulate; also fails opaquely if `Process.Start(...)` returns null when `dotnet` is missing from PATH (`!` triggers `NullReferenceException`). Wrap body in try/finally with `Directory.Delete(tempRoot, recursive: true)` and replace `!` with `?? throw new InvalidOperationException("dotnet CLI not found on PATH")`.
+- [x] [Review][Patch] `LocateRepositoryRoot` breaks on single-file publish [`tests/Hexalith.Folders.Client.Tests/ClientGenerationTests.cs:1891-1907`] — `Assembly.Location` returns `""` under single-file publish, then `Path.GetDirectoryName("")` returns `null`, then `new DirectoryInfo(null!)` throws `ArgumentNullException`. Fall back to `AppContext.BaseDirectory` when `Location` is empty.
+- [x] [Review][Patch] `EnumerableExtensions` declared in global namespace [`tests/Hexalith.Folders.Client.Tests/ClientGenerationTests.cs:1951-1964`] — pollutes the assembly's root namespace. Wrap in `namespace Hexalith.Folders.Client.Tests`.
+- [x] [Review][Patch] `Hexalith.Folders.Client.Generation.csproj` missing `<TargetFramework>` [`src/Hexalith.Folders.Client/Generation/Hexalith.Folders.Client.Generation.csproj`] — relies entirely on `Directory.Build.props` to provide one. If the props file changes default TFM or the project moves, `dotnet run --project ...` fails with a confusing error. Add an explicit `<TargetFramework>net10.0</TargetFramework>` (or whichever the project requires).
+- [x] [Review][Patch] `MutatingRequestsExposeIdempotencyHelpersAndQueriesDoNot` only asserts parameter count and return type [`tests/Hexalith.Folders.Client.Tests/ClientGenerationTests.cs:1532-1556`] — does NOT verify parameter names or order match the spine-derived path-parameter list. A future regression that swaps parameter order (as D3 demonstrates is plausible) silently passes. Assert both parameter names (camelCased from the spine path parameter names) and their order.
+- [x] [Review][Patch] `.lscache` IDE/build-cache files committed [`src/Hexalith.Folders.Client/Hexalith.Folders.Client.csproj.lscache`, `tests/Hexalith.Folders.Client.Tests/Hexalith.Folders.Client.Tests.csproj.lscache`] — outside the declared File List; auto-maintained machine-local cache. Add `*.lscache` to `.gitignore` (or the project-level git attributes) and remove both files from the diff.
+- [x] [Review][Patch] `RejectDuplicateProperties` throws `JsonReaderException` after deserialization [`src/Hexalith.Folders.Client/Idempotency/HexalithIdempotencyHasher.cs:1424`] — no reader is involved at that point; the JToken graph is in memory. Replace with `InvalidOperationException` to match the actual failure context.
+- [x] [Review][Patch] Generator placeholder substitution does not assert single occurrence [`src/Hexalith.Folders.Client/Generation/Program.cs:529-535`] — `output.IndexOf(placeholder)` finds the first match; if any rendered comment or string literal contains the literal `__GENERATED_HELPERS_SHA256__` a second time, only the first is replaced and the file no longer matches its own hash. Add a count check and fail-closed if `≠ 1`.
+- [x] [Review][Patch] `IdempotencyField.Value` accepts control characters even when the corpus labels them parser-rejected [`src/Hexalith.Folders.Client/Idempotency/HexalithIdempotencyHasher.cs:105-129`, `tests/fixtures/idempotency-encoding-corpus.json` malformed-idempotency-key-control-character case] — the canonical Escape table passes U+0001 through; corpus labels it parser-rejected. Reject C0/C1 control characters (and U+2028/U+2029, BOM) at the hasher boundary so the corpus classification matches actual behavior.
+- [x] [Review][Patch] `Escape` does not handle UTF-16 surrogate halves [`src/Hexalith.Folders.Client/Idempotency/HexalithIdempotencyHasher.cs:105-129`] — lone or split surrogates (truncated emoji, malformed input) produce invalid UTF-8 when the canonical string is hashed. Enumerate via `Rune.EnumerateRunes` and reject invalid surrogates explicitly.
+- [x] [Review][Patch] `double.ToString("R")` is platform-variant [`src/Hexalith.Folders.Client/Idempotency/HexalithIdempotencyHasher.cs:152-160`] — "R" round-trip format has varied across .NET versions for borderline IEEE-754 values. Replace with `BitConverter.DoubleToInt64Bits(value).ToString("x16", InvariantCulture)` (and similarly for float via `SingleToInt32Bits`) for deterministic bit-exact encoding.
+- [x] [Review][Patch] `TryReadProblemDetails` catches `JsonException` but not `JsonSerializationException` [`src/Hexalith.Folders.Client/Generated/HexalithFoldersIdempotencyHelpers.g.cs:108-118`] — Newtonsoft's `JsonSerializationException` is the type thrown for wrong-shape JSON (array, scalar) and is *not* always a subclass of `JsonException`. Catch `Newtonsoft.Json.JsonException` explicitly OR catch both types so adapters always see the structured diagnostic.
+- [x] [Review][Patch] `NormalizeJsonText` does not strip leading BOM [`src/Hexalith.Folders.Client/Idempotency/HexalithIdempotencyHasher.cs:65-79`] — UTF-8 BOM (U+FEFF) at the start of incoming JSON causes `JsonTextReader` to error or accept it as data. Strip the BOM before constructing the reader so payloads from BOM-prefixing producers hash equivalently.
+- [x] [Review][Patch] Corpus classification coverage incomplete [`tests/Hexalith.Folders.Client.Tests/ClientGenerationTests.cs:1686-1702`] — the if/else chain handles `non-equivalent`, `equivalent-only`, `parser-rejected`, `equivalent-after-lexicographic-field-ordering` only. `equivalent-after-generated-normalization-for-declared-normalization-insensitive-field` and `equivalent-only-when-field-declares-compatibility-normalization` fall through silently — fixture-consumed claim is partially false. Add an explicit branch for each remaining classification, OR throw on unknown classification to force coverage updates when the corpus gains new categories.
